
# 🔹 HTML Elements I Used

* **`<html>`** → Root element of the document.
* **`<head>`** → Contains metadata and links CSS files.
* **`<link>`** → Connects external CSS file and Bootstrap.
* **`<body>`** → Contains visible content.
* **`<div>`** → Background container (`.bg`) and card container (`.card-container`).
* **`<h1>`** → Main heading (“Advanced Technologies”).
* **`<p>`** → Description under the heading.
* **`<button>`** → Call-to-action buttons (“Learn More” and “Save Draft”).

---

# 🔹 CSS Properties I Used

* **`background-image`** → Sets the hero section background.
* **`background-size`** → Ensures background covers the container fully.
* **`height` / `width`** → Controls size of background and card containers.
* **`font-family`** → Applies custom fonts like Roboto and Bree Serif.
* **`font-size`** / **`font-style`** / **`font-weight`** → Styles headings and description.
* **`color`** → Sets text color for heading, description, and buttons.
* **`padding`** → Adds spacing inside card container and buttons.
* **`margin`** → Adds spacing between buttons and elements.
* **`border-radius`** → Rounds corners of card container and buttons.
* **Bootstrap Flex (`d-flex`, `flex-column`, `flex-row`, `justify-content-end`)** → Positions card at the bottom and arranges buttons horizontally.
* **`background-color`** → Colors card container and buttons for contrast.

---


